<paragraph id="8BAE1F43FFF8FFE46849FB26808AA280" blockId="30.[826,1441,1213,1754]" box="[826,945,1213,1234]" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE46849FB26808AA280" box="[826,945,1213,1234]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">Comments</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAE1F43FFF8FFE46849FB408790A088" blockId="30.[826,1441,1213,1754]" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">
This enigmatic species, restricted to 
<collectingCountry id="F3065FD3FFF8FFE46F89FB40860DA2A3" box="[1274,1334,1243,1265]" name="Cuba" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">Cuba</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F3065FD3FFF8FFE46E0FFB40808DA35D" name="Dominican Republic" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">the Dominican</collectingCountry>
Republic, has some idiosyncratic features, such as a heavily sclerotized plate dorsal to the anellus (transtila?), as well as the juxta and subscaphium heavily sclerotized, and the posterior arms of the gnathos fused together, enclosing the anal tube. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="4C1164C0FFF8FFE4688CFA088765A3F5" baseAuthorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[1023,1118,1426,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Ircila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hecate">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE4688CFA088732A3FA" box="[1023,1033,1427,1448]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">I</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE46F64FA098765A3F5" box="[1047,1118,1426,1447]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">hecate</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares some common features, such as the morphology of the gnathos, with the 
<taxonomicName id="4C1164C0FFF8FFE46801FA4B80FEA3B7" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[882,965,1488,1509]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Telchin" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE46801FA4B80FEA3B7" box="[882,965,1488,1509]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">Telchin</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, and plesiomorphic characters, such as the valva morphology, with 
<taxonomicName id="4C1164C0FFF8FFE46E60FA74865FA056" authorityName="Schaufuss" authorityYear="1870" box="[1299,1380,1519,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Ceretes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE46E60FA74865FA056" box="[1299,1380,1519,1540]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">Ceretes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1164C0FFF8FFE46849F99680F3A070" box="[826,968,1549,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Corybanthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE46849F99680F3A070" box="[826,968,1549,1570]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">Corybanthes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Concerning the forewing pattern, this genus has some patterns similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1164C0FFF8FFE46FAEF9B78656A012" authorityName="Moraes &amp; Duarte" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Godart" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[1245,1389,1579,1601]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Geyeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decussata">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE46FAEF9B787CBA013" box="[1245,1264,1580,1601]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE46F8DF9B08656A012" box="[1278,1389,1579,1600]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">decussata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the translucent subapical spots that are also present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C1164C0FFF8FFE4682AF9F280AEA02C" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1819" box="[857,917,1641,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Athis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE4682AF9F280AEA02C" box="[857,917,1641,1662]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">Athis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C1164C0FFF8FFE468A2F9F28750A02D" box="[977,1131,1641,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Castniidae" genus="Hista" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B965C351FFF8FFE468A2F9F28734A02C" box="[977,1039,1641,1662]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="392">Hista</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, but these are homoplastic characters. The sister-group relationship with a suprageneric clade was considered in our decision to maintain this monotypic genus.
</paragraph>
